dit></media:credit><media:title>Londoners pessimistic about Prime Minister Starmer&#39;s future</media:title><media:player url="https://www.nbcnews.com/video/londoners-pessimistic-about-prime-minister-starmer-s-future-263147589969"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/starmer_0512-nx4pj8.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">Londoners were pessimistic over Prime Minister Keir Starmer’s future after his Labour Party suffered heavy losses in local elections across the U.K.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/f_mo_lon_starmer_londoners_260512_0550.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/f_mo_lon_starmer_londoners_260512_0550.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/starmer_0512-nx4pj8.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 09:39:50 GMT</pubDate><title>Londoners pessimistic about Prime Minister Starmer&#39;s future</title><updateDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 10:02:39 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Alexandra Marquez</dc:creator><dc:creator>Bridget Bowman</dc:creator><dc:creator>Ben Kamisar</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 12 May 2026 09:00:42 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Tuesday’s primary elections in Nebraska will set the stage for November in a battleground House district, as well as a potentially competitive Senate contest, as Democrats try to win control of Congress.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/nebraska-west-virginia-primaries-midterms-2026-house-senate-elections-rcna344471</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/nebraska-west-virginia-primaries-midterms-2026-house-senate-elections-rcna344471</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-07/250703-don-bacon-se-428p-e78b66.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Frank Thorp V</media:credit><media:text type="plain">“There’s some things I wish were better,” Bacon said. “But am I going to vote to raise taxes on middle-class Americans? I’m not.”</media:text><media:description type="plain">Retiring Republican Rep. Don Bacon&#39;s Nebraska district will be a key battleground for both parties in the fight for the House majority. </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-02/260213-John-Cavanaugh-ew-212p-021dea.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Alex Wroblewski</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Nebraska Democratic State Senator John Cavanaugh</media:text><media:description type="plain">Retiring Republican Rep. Don Bacon&#39;s Nebraska district will be a key battleground for both parties in the fight for the House majority. </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260511-denise-powell-for-congress-vl-346p-2d55d2.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1366" width="2048"><media:credit>Denise Powell for Congress</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Denise Powell stands inside of a room smiling with her arms cross</media:text><media:description type="plain">Retiring Republican Rep. Don Bacon&#39;s Nebraska district will be a key battleground for both parties in the fight for the House majority. </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260511-cindy-burbank-william-forbes-nebraska-mb-1126-25b126.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="800" width="1200"><media:credit>cindyburbank.com; forbesfornebraska</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Cindy Burbank and William Forbes are facing off in Nebraska&#39;s Democratic Senate primary. </media:text><media:description type="plain">Retiring Republican Rep. Don Bacon&#39;s Nebraska district will be a key battleground for both parties in the fight for the House majority. </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2024-01/240130-Shelley-Moore-Capito-se-1129a-59c2ff.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Drew Angerer</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Sen. Shelley Moore Capito, R-W.V., speaks during a news conference </media:text><media:description type="plain">Retiring Republican Rep. Don Bacon&#39;s Nebraska district will be a key battleground for both parties in the fight for the House majority. </media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-07/250703-don-bacon-se-428p-e78b66.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 09:00:42 GMT</pubDate><title>Tuesday’s primaries to set up key fall matchups in Nebraska</title><updateDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 09:00:42 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Tyler Kingkade</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Liz Kreutz</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Daniella Silva</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 12 May 2026 09:00:43 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>A growing number of families and educators say they’re fed up with i-Ready’s personalized math and reading lessons, which feature repetitive cartoons and slow voice-overs.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/education/iready-school-software-faces-parent-teacher-student-fury-rcna342850</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/education/iready-school-software-faces-parent-teacher-student-fury-rcna342850</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260511-i-ready-zk-0921-fa3f2b.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Jenna Schoenefeld for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Ward Wooden, 14, demonstrates a math session on i-Ready at his family’s home in Studio City, CA, on Monday, May 11, 2026. </media:text><media:description type="plain">Ward Wooden, 14, demonstrates a math lesson on i-Ready at his family’s home in Studio City, Calif.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260511-i-ready-zk-0944-f1005f.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Jenna Schoenefeld for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Ward shows how an i-Ready game works on his school-issued Chromebook.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ward Wooden, 14, demonstrates a math lesson on i-Ready at his family’s home in Studio City, Calif.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260421-LAUSD-screenvote-4-ew-757p-1da071.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Jenna Schoenefeld for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Parents cheer the passing of a resolution to limit screen time at a recent Los Angeles school board meeting.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ward Wooden, 14, demonstrates a math lesson on i-Ready at his family’s home in Studio City, Calif.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260511-i-ready-zk-0925-c3adae.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="3126" width="2500"><media:credit>Jenna Schoenefeld for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Ward and his friends&#39; frequent complaints about i-Ready prompted his father to research the program.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ward Wooden, 14, demonstrates a math lesson on i-Ready at his family’s home in Studio City, Calif.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-i-ready-ww-1136-9788ca.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Jenna Schoenefeld for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A bald man with black eyeglasses rests his chin on one hand while seated at a desk in a bedroom.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ward Wooden, 14, demonstrates a math lesson on i-Ready at his family’s home in Studio City, Calif.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-i-ready-ww-1138-086c6c.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="2500" width="1667"><media:credit>Jenna Schoenefeld for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A goateed man wearing a checkered shirt standing for a portrait in the shade.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ward Wooden, 14, demonstrates a math lesson on i-Ready at his family’s home in Studio City, Calif.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260511-Curriculum-Associates-Rob-Waldron-mn-1415-667621.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1615" width="2423"><media:credit>Keith Bedford</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Curriculum Associates CEO Rob Waldron</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ward Wooden, 14, demonstrates a math lesson on i-Ready at his family’s home in Studio City, Calif.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-i-ready-Jonathan-Kryk-1x1-ww-1131-f24a4b.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="450" width="450"><media:credit>Courtesy Jonathan Kryk</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A young man holding an award certificate and smiling broadly.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ward Wooden, 14, demonstrates a math lesson on i-Ready at his family’s home in Studio City, Calif.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-i-ready-ww-1125-e3c715.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Jenna Schoenefeld for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A person seen from the waist down holding a hand-written sign reading Save Our Kids. </media:text><media:description type="plain">Ward Wooden, 14, demonstrates a math lesson on i-Ready at his family’s home in Studio City, Calif.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260421-LAUSD-screenvote-1-ew-757p-38a2f7.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Jenna Schoenefeld for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Bridie Lee&#39;s son reads a Garfield comic book during an LAUSD board meeting, waiting for his turn to speak in the public comment session.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ward Wooden, 14, demonstrates a math lesson on i-Ready at his family’s home in Studio City, Calif.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260511-i-ready-zk-0921-fa3f2b.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 09:00:43 GMT</pubDate><title>Widely used educational software that many parents say makes kids ‘miserable’ faces backlash</title><updateDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 09:00:43 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 12 May 2026 11:21:38 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Jake Rosmarin, o